  "title": "MANUFACTURING OPERATIONS MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>The Manufacturing Operations Manager will be responsible for overseeing the production process to ensure that output meets quality expectations as well as customer demands. They will manage operations and maintenance staff while conducting operational workflow and identifying areas of process improvement. Additionally, they will be tasked with ensuring compliance with health and safety standards, managing budgets, and tracking performance metrics.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee production process from start to finish ensuring output meets quality and customer requirements</li><li>Manage operations and maintenance staff ensuring they have the necessary training and resources to perform their duties</li><li>Review operational workflow, identifying areas of process improvement, and implementing necessary changes</li><li>Ensure compliance with health and safety standards as well as any legal regulations</li><li>Manage budgets for production and maintenance, ensuring expenses remain within approved limits</li><li>Track performance metrics, identify areas of underperformance, and create plans to\nimprove operations</li><li>Provide regular updates to Senior Management on production status and performance metric\n<strong> </strong></li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Relevant experience in a manufacturing environment with staff management responsibilities</li><li>Strong communication, leadership, and problem-solving skills</li><li>Ability to work well under pressure and prioritize tasks effectively</li><li>Proficient in industry-specific software and technology</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
